From: Beast <beast@mono-gateway.local>
Date: Wed, 26 Mar 2026 21:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] soc: fsl: qbman: Add USDPAA mainline driver for DPDK

Add a clean implementation of /dev/fsl-usdpaa and /dev/fsl-usdpaa-irq
character devices that provide the NXP USDPAA ioctl ABI for DPDK's
DPAA1 PMD, built against mainline BMan/QMan APIs instead of the NXP
SDK kernel.

Implements:
 - Resource allocation: BPID, FQID, pool-channel, CGRID ranges
 - Portal reservation: physical addresses for userspace mmap
 - DMA memory: allocation from reserved-memory DT node
 - Link status: queries via net_device carrier state
 - Stash configuration: via qman_set_sdest()
 - Full FD cleanup on close (portals, resources, DMA)
 - Portal mmap with pgprot_cached_nonshared() for CE windows
   and pgprot_noncached() for CI windows (ARM64-safe)

Resource release uses allocator-only free functions (bm_free_bpid_range,
qman_free_fqid_range, qman_free_pool_range, qman_free_cgrid_range)
to avoid kernel panics when portals are reserved for userspace.

The ioctl numbers and structure layouts are binary-compatible with
NXP's fsl_usdpaa.h, so unmodified DPDK binaries can use this driver.

CEETM, link status interrupts, and link speed control are stubbed
(-ENOSYS or no-op) as DPDK does not use them.

Tested: dpdk-testpmd runs 30s clean on kernel #23, clean exit + reboot
with zero kernel panics on LS1046A Mono Gateway.

Signed-off-by: Beast <beast@mono-gateway.local>
---
 drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Kconfig               |   12 +
 drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Makefile              |    1 +
 drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/fsl_usdpaa_mainline.c | 1453 ++++++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 1466 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/fsl_usdpaa_mainline.c

diff --git a/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Kconfig b/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Kconfig
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Kconfig
@@ -XXX,4 +XXX,16 @@
 	  QBMan is the Queue and Buffer Manager block in DPAA networking
 	  architecture. Needed to support the DPAA networking drivers.
 
+config FSL_USDPAA_MAINLINE
+	tristate "Userspace DPAA driver for DPDK"
+	depends on FSL_DPAA
+	help
+	  Provides /dev/fsl-usdpaa character device for DPDK's DPAA1 PMD.
+	  Allows userspace applications to allocate QBMan resources (BPIDs,
+	  FQIDs, pool channels, CGRIDs), reserve portals for direct hardware
+	  access, and manage DMA memory from reserved-memory regions.
+
+	  Required for DPDK with the dpaa bus driver.
+
+	  If unsure, say N.
 endif # FSL_DPAA

diff --git a/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Makefile b/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Makefile
index XXXXXXX..XXXXXXX 100644
--- a/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/Makefile
@@ -XXX,3 +XXX,4 @@
 obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_DPAA)                          += bman_ccsr.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_DPAA)                          += bman_portal.o
 obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_DPAA)                          += bman.o
+obj-$(CONFIG_FSL_USDPAA_MAINLINE)               += fsl_usdpaa_mainline.o

NOTE: The source file fsl_usdpaa_mainline.c is maintained separately in
data/kernel-patches/fsl_usdpaa_mainline.c and must be copied to
drivers/soc/fsl/qbman/ during the build. This avoids maintaining a
1453-line unified diff that would be impossible to review.

The build script (auto-build.yml or bin/build-usdpaa-mainline.sh) copies
the file after applying this patch.
